ify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The site is in a green belt area and the proposed alterations to the buildings and grounds would result in the erosion of the Green Belt. Additionally the site is within the Metropolitan Green Belt where there is a presumption against development, except </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for a specified list of categories. This development does not fall within those categories. Any permitted exception to these restrictions would indicate a relaxing of these checks and must therefore increase the risk of further intrusion into the Green Bel</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t by other developments.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he area has very poor transport provision and this development must therefore result in a large increase in traffic in order to accommodate the transportation of 850 pupils plus possibly 100 staff on a twice daily basis</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, plus </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">evening and weekend activities.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Stoke </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Poges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is a small village numbering some 5000 residents. It is quite apparent that the vast majority of residents are totally opposed to the imposition of this school in the village.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The intention, it would seem, was to apply to open the school in Slough, Be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rkshire, and approval was given </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o proceed. This scheme, in my opinion, was the logical decision since the school is intended for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">pupils</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">residing in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Berkshire and West London </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Boroughs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. There is no requirement for extra school places in the area of Stoke </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Poges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, and therefore it is an illogical decision to site the school in this village where it will provide no benefits to the community </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">whatsosever</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The decision to apply for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the school in Stoke </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Poges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and the subsequent decision to support that proposal seems to fly in the face of government’s efforts to control green house gases by reducing unnecessary travel by motor vehicles, when there ar</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e locations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> within</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Slough, Berkshir</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e and West London that could </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">accomodate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> this school.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Concerns regarding the flawed manner in which the Consultation was carried out</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The consultation would h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ve bordered on the farci</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cal if it were not for the fact that it consisted, for the most part, on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">deceit and subterfuge.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he school was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">promoted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">everywhere but in South Bucks. A meeting arranged for parents of both Slough and West London was not offered to South Bucks residents.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The statutory 6 week public consultation started with a link </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">online form displayed on the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Khalsa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Secondary Academy </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Facebook</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. However, no notification was made to Stoke </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Poges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Parish Council or any local South Bucks Residents</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> An Open Evening was held </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">at Pioneer House for both local residents and prospective pare</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nts with differing consultation forms for residents and prospective parents</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Sikhsangat.com website leaked possible consultation results before end date.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> A Public Meeting </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">set up in response to a request by Mr </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Kandola</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and SSET</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to have an opportunity to talk to residents and answer their questions. At the last minute both SSET and Mr. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Kandola</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> declined to participate.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">6.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Less than 36 hours before an SBDC Planning Committee meeting both the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">DfE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and the proposer advised SBDC that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">their Planning Application would be withdrawn and they would rely on new Permitted Development rights.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">7. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Mike </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Appleyard</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, Deputy Leader And Cabinet Member for Education stated that there was no requirement </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or need for a Secondary School and opposed the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">location of the school.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">8.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Over 5000 named petitions from Stoke </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Poges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> residents opposing the school</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">presented to  Downing Street and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">DfE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">The question of democratic process.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">From the above factual summary I would have thought that there was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">sufficient reason to take into account the very strong protests of the majority of the residents of Stoke </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Poges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, together with the statements of both Dominic Grieve MP and Mike </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Appleyard</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, Deputy Leader and Cabinet Member for Education,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that the School shou</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ld not be located in Stoke </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Poges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and as a result refuse this</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> proposal.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We live in a country that is a world leader in advocating the pursuit of democracy. However, I am bound to say that the word appears to be open to varying interpretations depending on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">who is advocating it. To me the word means that democracy is the legal exercise of the will of the people. In other words, where the people are consulted, a decision is made to act upon the wishes of the majority of those people. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Unfortunately, it would appear that in the case of the Sikh </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Khalsa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Academy application, the government is happy to pay lip service to the people by carrying out a consultation and then, regardless of the wishes of the people, carry out what they always int</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ended to do. One cannot wonder whether the new Permitted Development rights are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nothing but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a cynical</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> ploy </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">used by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">government, its aim being the express intention of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> circumvent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the normal rules of democracy.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I am reminded of Chaucer’s words “One ear he</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ard it, and at the other it went out”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">The Gradual Erosion of the Green Belt</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Finally, recently on BBC Radio 4, it was interesting to hear that a number of respected Green</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Organisations, which included those such as the Royal Society for the Protection of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Birds, have accused the Government of failing to ensure the protection of Green Belt areas by permitting intrusions into protected Green Belt areas throughout the country.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Perhaps this does not bode well for the Green Belt in Stoke </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Poges</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">What a brave New</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> World we now live in!</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>